I'm sure you've heard that abs are "made in the kitchen". 💯With that being true, I would include that abs are more so made in the gym but revealed through clean eating. 
One still needs those abdominal muscles to be strengthened and developed in order to attain what most refer to as "a deadly 6-pack". 😎

I personally train abs 2-3 times a week via 12-14 sets of 15-20 reps. 
I use a different combinations of exercises to ensure I am well rounded and balanced. Some of my favourites are:

1️⃣ Hanging Leg Raise
2️⃣ Cable Crunches
3️⃣ Stability Ball Rockers
4️⃣ Anti-Rotation Movements (with R-Band)
5️⃣ Decline Crunches
